        {
          "reviewTitle": "Pretty darn good for drugstore foundation",
          "reviewText": "I ordered L15 and L30 (warm light shades) to mix because I always need to mix drugstore foundations to achieve a match for my NC20 skin. But, this shade range is incredible and L30 was all I needed!! It goes on two shades lighter than it dries down to so don't let the wet shade scare you. So, I guess it oxidizes? To me, it just dries down. At first I used it over moisturizer, no primer, just to see how it would work out and it was kind of cakey and sort of uneven.looking. But, over primer (i'm currently using NYX Shine Free- transparent and siliconey) and it looks really well all day. Not cakey or uneven at all. I do wish it had slightly better coverage but it layers well. At this point, however, if I have to use three pumps, I might as well just buy MAC Studio Fix liquid because while it's more expensive, I need to use far less and it's just a better foundation. But, if you want the convenience of the drugstore, have oily skin or just like a matte finish and don't want anything more than a light/medium coverage, this is a great foundation! It dries slightly chalky, it's definitely drugstore quality, it reminds me a bit of the Rimmel matte in the tube, but I use a dewy but long lasting setting spray and illuminating powders to counter the dry look and it lasts all day and looks pretty well, really. For the price and colour match, you can't go wrong.",
